         <div type="translation" resp="part:kuch">
           <p n="1">Venerable Āryadatta.</p>
            </div>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>The three lotus pedestals bearing the inscription are on the pedestal of a seated Buddha statue. The inscription is written on the back of the statue and upside down. As G. Coedès suggests, the name should be the statue's founder's rather than that of the statue and the honorific title <foreign>pu caḥ Añ</foreign> is the equivalent de <foreign>sthavira</foreign> as attested in the inscription of Vat Prei Veal.</p>
         </div>
